"Poured from a bottle into a shaker pint, the beer is a bright, slightly hazed, goldenrod coloring with a steady flow of carbonation throughout the body, and a tall, fluffy, bubbly, white head that settles out fairly quick. Aromas of toasted grains, subtle banana sweetness, nutmeg and clove spices, bready notes, and a subtle butterscotch sweetness. Flavors are fairly smooth and balanced, with a rich and sweet caramel and butterscotch blend forward, laced with light clove and nutmeg spices, toasted notes, hints of Belgian yeast esters and funk, and some sweet banana characteristics. The body is mid-range, but the carbonation keeps it crisp and slightly dry. The aftertaste is more of the roast and banana characteristics. Smooth, dry, somewhat crisp finish. Not bad."
