"I actually enjoyed this one a lot. Some distinctive stuff going on (at least from my previous experiences). Poured a straw-color from the 12oz into my snifter, definitely unfiltered, definitely very little in the way of head. A hint of pear, and a ton of white grape/white wine aromas on the nose. Just a hint of the yeast, clean and subtle. Bit sour on the front of the sip, with some surprisingly bright notes emerging. Refreshing. Just a hint of warmth on the back end. Crisp and dry mouthfeel, and the bit of lingering aftertaste was very style-appropriate. Very different take on the Belgian to me (I am used to mostly trippels and quads), and very glad I picked this one up!"
