"Taste/feel: Medium feel with a moderate/low carbonation. The taste is much like the smell. Faintness all-around with clove being at the forefront with a little bit of banana, and then a little bit of corn-like adjunct flavor. Finishes clean, but overall ""bleh."" It tastes rather light (as I'd expect given the ABV) and isn't at all blowing me away like I thought these Planet Series beers would -- Mars did, but both this and Venus have been let downs. Anyway, the taste is light with no real intensity, it's just loaded with subtly. That's not normally a bad thing, but this is just a ""meh"" beer that's the very definitely of decent. Not only did I expect something fantastic from Bell's, I anticipated something pretty much earth shattering, since it's the Planet Series. I could deal with Venus being one of those adventurous beers that couldn't quite make it, but this is just a ho-hum Belgian Pale Ale that I paid $3 for just because of the label. Oh well. Like Venus, I know not to buy it again. This series is turning out to be a disappointment so far. I think this beer (and probably Venus as well) would score lower had they not been Bell's Planet Series beers. This beer should've just been called ""Bell's Mediocrity."""
